Major News Items in Leading Turkish Newspapers
ANKARA , November 19 ( Xinhua ) -- The following are major news items in leading Turkish newspapers Thursday .
Milliyet ( National ) :
-- Turkish Parliament Wednesday adopted a declaration , calling on the Italian government to extradite Abdullah Ocalan , leader of the outlawed Kurdish Workers ' Party ( PKK ) , to Turkey .
" Turkey wants the cruel murderer who killed 30,000 people to be punished within the framework of the laws , " the declaration said .
Sabah ( Morning ) :
-- Describing Ocalan as " a brutal terrorist , " U.S. State Department spokesman James Rubin has asked Italy not to grant political asylum to the PKK leader .
He urged Italian government to extradite Ocalan to Turkey , saying that Ocalan 's statement that the PKK will give up terrorism is an out-and-out lie .
Hurriyet ( Freedom ) :
-- Addressing the Austrian-Turkish Business Council in Vienna Wednesday , Turkish President Suleyman Demirel said that Turkey should be regarded as a part of Europe .
He expressed the hope that Turkey would be invited to the European Union summit to be held in Vienna in mid-December .
